Size:   Finished Length 22" Geode 19x22 mm depth 9mm just under an inch 

Geodes are essentially hollow, spherical  masses of mineral matter that may form from either the filling of gas bubbles in volcanic to sub-volcanic rocks by minerals deposited from hydrothermal fluids. They commonly have a chalcedony ( quartz) shell lined internally by various minerals, often as crystals, particularly calcite, pyrite, kaolinite and  quartz, which is by far the most common and abundant mineral found in geodes.
